com.uber.rib.core

Interface RouterNavigator<StateT extends RouterNavigatorState>

  • Type Parameters:
    StateT - type of state to switch on.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ModernRouterNavigator

    public interface RouterNavigator<StateT extends RouterNavigatorState>
    Simple utility for switching a child router based on a state.

      • popState

        void popState()
        Pop the current state and rewind to the previous state (if there is a previous state).

      • pushRetainedState

        <R extends com.uber.rib.core.Router> void pushRetainedState(StateT newState,
                                                            RouterNavigator.AttachTransition<R,StateT> attachTransition,
                                                            @Nullable
                                                            RouterNavigator.DetachTransition<R,StateT> detachTransition)
        Switch to a new state - this will switch out children if the state if not the current active state already.

        NOTE: This will retain the Riblet in memory until it is popped. To push transient, riblets, use pushTransientState(RouterNavigatorState, AttachTransition, DetachTransition)

        Type Parameters:
        R - router type to detach.
        Parameters:
        newState - to switch to.
        attachTransition - method to attach child router.
        detachTransition - method to clean up child router when removed.

        NOTE: This will retain the Riblet in memory until it is popped. To push transient, riblets, use pushTransientState(RouterNavigatorState, AttachTransition, DetachTransition)

      • pushTransientState

        <R extends com.uber.rib.core.Router> void pushTransientState(StateT newState,
                                                             RouterNavigator.AttachTransition<R,StateT> attachTransition,
                                                             @Nullable
                                                             RouterNavigator.DetachTransition<R,StateT> detachTransition)
        Switch to a new transient state - this will switch out children if the state if not the current active state already.

        NOTE: Transient states do not live in the back navigation stack.

        Type Parameters:
        R - router type to detach.
        Parameters:
        newState - to switch to.
        attachTransition - method to attach child router.
        detachTransition - method to clean up child router when removed.
